## Rewrite Rules

1. Preserve the same top-level fields and output the full theory.
2. Keep every premise sentence's `nl` unchanged and keep premise order unchanged.
3. Keep the query `nl` unchanged.
4. Fix the logical structure by editing `logic`, `symbols`, and `background` only where needed.
5. Use compact DSL top-level fields: `symbols`, `sentences`, `query`, `background`.
6. Each sentence/query/background `logic` must be a compact logic string (not nested AST JSON).
7. Allowed syntax: `p(x)`, `f(x)==y`, `x!=y`, `and(...)`, `or(...)`, `not(...)`, `implies(a,b)`, `iff(a,b)`, `forall x:S. body`, `exists x:S. body`, `eq(a,b)`, `ne(a,b)`.
8. Default to one object-domain sort `Entity`; represent type/category via unary predicates.
9. Use numeric literals only for numeric sorts (`Int`/`Real`/`BitVec`); otherwise use named constants.
10. Use identifier-safe symbol names only (`[A-Za-z_][A-Za-z0-9_]*`).
11. Do not output `sentence_index`, `role`, `kind`, `constraint`, `forall`, or `exists` wrapper fields.
12. Do not use raw boolean atoms like `"true"` or `"false"`.
13. Do not use assignment-style atoms like `"x = y"`; use `"x == y"`.
